---
description: Architecture rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Before generating code:

1. Design architecture.
2. Define services.
3. Define controllers.
4. Define remotes.
5. Define shared modules.
6. Explain networking flow.
7. Generate implementation.

Use:

Service Layer
Controller Layer
Shared Layer
Feature Modules (pluggable elements — see roblox-feature-modules.mdc)

Business logic belongs only in Services (or Feature Behaviors on the server).

Orchestrator services (e.g. CampService) MUST delegate feature-specific logic to registries — never inline `if featureId == ...`.

Controllers:

- UI
- Input
- Camera
- Sound

Never place business logic inside controllers.